Print convex_biclustering Results

Source: R/solvers.R
print.ConvexBiClustering.Rd

Prints a brief descripton of a fitted convex_biclustering object.

# S3 method for ConvexBiClustering
print(x, ...)

Arguments

x

an object of class convex_biclustering as returned by convex_biclustering
...

Additional unused arguments

Details

Reports number of observations and variables of dataset, any preprocessing done by the convex_biclustering function, and regularization details.

Examples

bicluster_fit <- convex_biclustering(presidential_speech, lambda_grid = 1:5)
#> Pre-computing column weights and edge sets
#> Pre-computing row weights and edge sets
#> Computing Convex Bi-Clustering Path
#> Post-processing
print(bicluster_fit)
#> Convex Clustering Fit Summary
#> =============================
#> 
#> Algorithm: ADMM [L2] 
#> Grid: 6 values of lambda. 
#> Fit Time: 0.656 secs 
#> Total Time: 0.781 secs 
#> 
#> Number of Rows: 44 
#> Number of Columns: 75 
#> 
#> Pre-processing options:
#>  - Global centering: TRUE 
#> 
#> Row Weights:
#>  - Source: Radial Basis Function Kernel Weights
#>  - Distance Metric: Euclidean
#>  - Scale parameter (phi): 0.01 [Data-Driven]
#>  - Sparsified: 4 Nearest Neighbors [Data-Driven]
#> 
#> Column Weights:
#>  - Source: Radial Basis Function Kernel Weights
#>  - Distance Metric: Euclidean
#>  - Scale parameter (phi): 0.01 [Data-Driven]
#>  - Sparsified: 2 Nearest Neighbors [Data-Driven]
#>
